    "comment": "Rationale: The taurine transporter transports taurine into neurons.\n\nTaurine transporter (TAUT) KO mice exhibit a strong reduction in the taurine concentration in different brain regions (Table 2). Taurine levels were determined from microdissected, homogenized tissue samples using an amino acid analyser.\n\n25/01/2018 Pim\n- Taurine is a modulator of LTP (Fig.1+2). KO of the taurine transporter strengthens this effect.. Experimental description: Genotyped 6- to 11-week-old TAUT KO (n= 11) and wild-type (WT, n= 10) mice...",
